>> CS: Yes, he's a young man
who grew-up in Eastern Europe

00:55:56.454 --> 00:56:03.060 align:middle line:84%
and then who came to the
States and ended by founding

00:56:03.060 --> 00:56:07.198 align:middle line:84%
or co-founding and organization
called Reciprocity that works

00:56:07.198 --> 00:56:12.403 align:middle line:84%
with homeless or
challenged young people,

00:56:12.403 --> 00:56:15.339 align:middle line:84%
but what is also very
interesting about his work is

00:56:15.339 --> 00:56:17.441 align:middle line:84%
that he takes -- he works
with these young people

00:56:17.441 --> 00:56:22.480 align:middle line:84%
to encourage them and
support them to discover how,

00:56:22.480 --> 00:56:25.316 align:middle line:84%
what is their passion and
vision to serve the world.

00:56:25.316 --> 00:56:28.219 align:middle line:84%
So it's not only how are
we going to help you,

00:56:28.219 --> 00:56:33.157 align:middle line:84%
but how are you going to find
your passion to help the world?

00:56:33.157 --> 00:56:34.558 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:56:34.558 --> 00:56:37.161 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: And then he trains people
in sacred spiritual activism,

00:56:37.161 --> 00:56:40.097 align:middle line:84%
so he trains a lot of these
young people, so it's like it's

00:56:40.097 --> 00:56:43.367 align:middle line:84%
that circle of everyone
is called to serve,

00:56:43.367 --> 00:56:45.102 align:middle line:84%
no one is just on
the receiving end.

00:56:45.102 --> 00:56:47.705 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: He was in his 20s
when he started this?

00:56:47.705 --> 00:56:49.173 align:middle line:90%
He's quite young, maybe 30?

00:56:49.173 --> 00:56:50.941 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: Yes, I would think so,
I can't tell you, but he's ...

00:56:50.941 --> 00:56:51.742 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: A young guy,
he's very young.

00:56:51.742 --> 00:56:52.676 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: ...

00:56:52.676 --> 00:56:53.377 align:middle line:84%
he's very young,
a very young guy.

00:56:53.377 --> 00:56:54.745 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Very passionate.

00:56:54.745 --> 00:56:56.480 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: And what is beautiful
about his story that touched me

00:56:56.480 --> 00:57:01.085 align:middle line:84%
so profoundly, you know, he
went to India I think on his way

00:57:01.085 --> 00:57:04.288 align:middle line:84%
to the States or something
like that, and he speaks

00:57:04.288 --> 00:57:10.161 align:middle line:84%
about one day he looked, he
saw the face of a young woman

00:57:10.161 --> 00:57:17.201 align:middle line:84%
that was in tremendous pain
and suffering extremely,

00:57:17.201 --> 00:57:21.505 align:middle line:84%
and he saw her there and
he reached out to her.

00:57:21.505 --> 00:57:23.207 align:middle line:90%
But he said that when he came

00:57:23.207 --> 00:57:27.411 align:middle line:84%
to the States I mean this
was the land of opportunity,

00:57:27.411 --> 00:57:29.880 align:middle line:84%
so we can come to the
States thinking, oh,

00:57:29.880 --> 00:57:31.549 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to create
a fortune, you know?

00:57:31.549 --> 00:57:32.349 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Right.

00:57:32.349 --> 00:57:33.117 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: I'm going to like ...

00:57:33.117 --> 00:57:34.218 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: That's number one.

00:57:34.218 --> 00:57:35.419 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: ...

00:57:35.419 --> 00:57:37.187 align:middle line:84%
become the ultimate
self-made person, you know?

00:57:37.187 --> 00:57:40.958 align:middle line:84%
But Adam, and who is smart, who
is energetic, was passionate,

00:57:40.958 --> 00:57:46.530 align:middle line:84%
said what guided was the
face of that woman I saw,

00:57:46.530 --> 00:57:49.099 align:middle line:84%
that's what became
my north star,

00:57:49.099 --> 00:57:52.770 align:middle line:84%
and then organized
his whole life.

00:57:52.770 --> 00:57:55.673 align:middle line:84%
That was an angel, and see
this is something we forget

00:57:55.673 --> 00:57:59.877 align:middle line:84%
sometimes, that angels can
appear as beautiful visions

00:57:59.877 --> 00:58:03.314 align:middle line:84%
of light or beautiful mountains,
I mean angels can appear

00:58:03.314 --> 00:58:07.818 align:middle line:84%
in that, but of course
when angels appear as those

00:58:07.818 --> 00:58:13.724 align:middle line:84%
who are most suffering among
us and who are awakening us

00:58:13.724 --> 00:58:15.793 align:middle line:90%
and awaken us to action.

00:58:15.793 --> 00:58:21.265 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: And you talk about
how you've seen the destitute

00:58:21.265 --> 00:58:24.268 align:middle line:84%
praying, please,
help, please, help.

00:58:24.268 --> 00:58:25.636 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: Yes.

00:58:25.636 --> 00:58:27.705 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: But you realized that
that was very empowering for you

00:58:27.705 --> 00:58:31.642 align:middle line:84%
to realize you're
part of the Divine,

00:58:31.642 --> 00:58:33.410 align:middle line:90%
that they're praying for.

00:58:33.410 --> 00:58:34.712 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: Yes.

00:58:34.712 --> 00:58:38.749 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: To and for, the help
has to come from among us,

00:58:38.749 --> 00:58:41.585 align:middle line:84%
the charity toward each
other, the enlightenment,

00:58:41.585 --> 00:58:44.088 align:middle line:84%
the assistance to
find our own truth.

00:58:44.088 --> 00:58:45.155 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: Right.

00:58:45.155 --> 00:58:46.423 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: From one to
the other, that's ...

00:58:46.423 --> 00:58:48.892 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: And working to end
all of this extreme power

00:58:48.892 --> 00:58:51.161 align:middle line:84%
and the extreme suffering
that --

00:58:51.161 --> 00:58:54.531 align:middle line:84%
you know, what really struck
me as a metaphor that I use

00:58:54.531 --> 00:58:59.570 align:middle line:84%
in my teaching, it's about
six people stuck in a room

00:58:59.570 --> 00:59:02.573 align:middle line:84%
that was burning and there
was one way out, which is one

00:59:02.573 --> 00:59:05.042 align:middle line:84%
of these '60s windows
that is up there?

00:59:05.042 --> 00:59:05.976 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

00:59:05.976 --> 00:59:07.344 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: And nobody
can reach to it,

00:59:07.344 --> 00:59:11.882 align:middle line:84%
so everybody huddled together
and one person climbs on all

00:59:11.882 --> 00:59:15.686 align:middle line:84%
of them and gets to the window,
and they say go get help,

00:59:15.686 --> 00:59:17.254 align:middle line:84%
you know, we're going to
help you get up there.

00:59:17.254 --> 00:59:20.224 align:middle line:84%
And so the person gets out of
the window and he goes out,

00:59:20.224 --> 00:59:21.925 align:middle line:84%
when he goes out
he sees the city

00:59:21.925 --> 00:59:24.361 align:middle line:84%
with its lights and
so on and so on.

00:59:24.361 --> 00:59:27.531 align:middle line:84%
And after, and he was hungry, he
gets a good hamburger, whatever,

00:59:27.531 --> 00:59:31.468 align:middle line:84%
or maybe a vegetarian
meal, and but then forgets

00:59:31.468 --> 00:59:33.604 align:middle line:84%
about the people,
forgets that they,

00:59:33.604 --> 00:59:35.773 align:middle line:84%
it's on their backs
that he got here.

00:59:35.773 --> 00:59:38.542 align:middle line:84%
And then he might go and be
a lector and do meditation

00:59:38.542 --> 00:59:42.546 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, but he forgets
that he wouldn't be here.

00:59:42.546 --> 00:59:46.684 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that every
one of us who is privileged,

00:59:46.684 --> 00:59:49.353 align:middle line:84%
we got there on the
back of those people,

00:59:49.353 --> 00:59:52.322 align:middle line:84%
they are the one
who brought us here.

00:59:52.322 --> 00:59:56.760 align:middle line:84%
I am one of them, I just have
-- happen to have more money

00:59:56.760 --> 01:00:00.364 align:middle line:84%
and more education and more
-- acquired some skills,

01:00:00.364 --> 01:00:04.368 align:middle line:84%
but I'm one of them, I need
to go back to that room

01:00:04.368 --> 01:00:07.871 align:middle line:84%
to end the fire because
if it wasn't for them none

01:00:07.871 --> 01:00:09.373 align:middle line:90%
of us would have come out.

01:00:09.373 --> 01:00:12.476 align:middle line:84%
I mean look at the
workers, the teachers ...

01:00:12.476 --> 01:00:12.976 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: True.

01:00:12.976 --> 01:00:13.644 align:middle line:90%
>> CS: ...

01:00:13.644 --> 01:00:14.978 align:middle line:90%
all of whom made us.

01:00:14.978 --> 01:00:20.217 align:middle line:84%
Yes, I put my own, but I am
at the top of the pyramid,

01:00:20.217 --> 01:00:22.619 align:middle line:90%
on the backs who got me here.

01:00:22.619 --> 01:00:25.055 align:middle line:84%
>> RM: Yes, what a
beautiful metaphor.

01:00:25.055 --> 01:00:27.324 align:middle line:84%
We only have a minute or
so left, what is the thing

01:00:27.324 --> 01:00:29.526 align:middle line:84%
that gives you the
greatest amount of hope

01:00:29.526 --> 01:00:33.197 align:middle line:84%
that the situation we're in,
sitting on this precipice,

01:00:33.197 --> 01:00:36.366 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, on a number of
levels, that we are going

01:00:36.366 --> 01:00:40.938 align:middle line:84%
to break-through and clearly
make it to the other side?

01:00:40.938 --> 01:00:45.309 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: Well, I don't know,
I don't know if we can know

01:00:45.309 --> 01:00:46.877 align:middle line:84%
if we're going to make
it to the other side,

01:00:46.877 --> 01:00:52.182 align:middle line:84%
but what gives me a lot
of hope is that we --

01:00:52.182 --> 01:00:55.285 align:middle line:84%
there is a great reformation
in our spirituality happening

01:00:55.285 --> 01:00:57.154 align:middle line:84%
in our mind toward
love and action.

01:00:57.154 --> 01:00:58.555 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes.

01:00:58.555 --> 01:01:01.625 align:middle line:84%
>> CS: And that, if we keep on
investing in that and teaching

01:01:01.625 --> 01:01:05.262 align:middle line:84%
that and teaching meditation
and action, love and action,

01:01:05.262 --> 01:01:08.365 align:middle line:84%
spirituality and action,
there are so many people

01:01:08.365 --> 01:01:11.535 align:middle line:84%
who are spiritual, or of faith
that is very loving faith,

01:01:11.535 --> 01:01:12.870 align:middle line:90%
that can make the difference.

01:01:12.870 --> 01:01:16.140 align:middle line:84%
And that can save us, but the
question is will we invest

01:01:16.140 --> 01:01:16.907 align:middle line:90%
in that?

01:01:16.907 --> 01:01:17.908 align:middle line:90%
Will we go fully in that?

01:01:17.908 --> 01:01:19.209 align:middle line:84%
It is coming out,
it is burgeoning,

01:01:19.209 --> 01:01:21.044 align:middle line:90%
the second layer is coming out,

01:01:21.044 --> 01:01:24.648 align:middle line:84%
but the question is will we
respond to it and invest in that

01:01:24.648 --> 01:01:27.351 align:middle line:84%
and start teaching and
writing about it and speaking

01:01:27.351 --> 01:01:29.119 align:middle line:90%
about it and making it happen?

01:01:29.119 --> 01:01:32.289 align:middle line:84%
And I think if it happens
it can shift the trajectory

01:01:32.289 --> 01:01:32.990 align:middle line:90%
of our world.

01:01:32.990 --> 01:01:34.625 align:middle line:90%
>> RM: Yes, yes, indeed.

01:01:34.625 --> 01:01:37.194 align:middle line:84%
Oh, it's such a pleasure
just spending a little bit

01:01:37.194 --> 01:01:38.028 align:middle line:90%
